column2: Beautiful Day 78.8 deg- thin overcast clouds- 3-fishing boats- Bald Eagle overhead- slight west wind.
Nice day- little cool 65.3 deg- thin overcast clouds- Moderate S.E. wind- 2-Fishing boats- 8-SeaGulls- 4-Mergansers. {Chem data collected and sent in also}
Partly cloudy- 76degs. Mild N. Wind. Two previous days were very windy (NW). Rain the previous night
Mostly sunny- Mild NNE wind- 77deg- 1 water ski boat. Lake is about 8" lower than noted on 7/5/04.
Few puffy clouds- light NE wind. 1 Bald Eagle above + 10 Mergansers in the lake. Lake is more green and cloudy than usual but no large algae blooms. [Chemistry also]
Sunny- no clouds 65deg. 1 fisher boat- 2 Loons beautiful day.
Sunny- 75 deg F- few clouds- Little rain for last 3 to 4 wks. A couple fishing boats on lake.
Sunny + hot 85 deg F. No one else on lake- light breeze- very few clouds-one Loon nearby. Lake lowest in over 10 years.
Sunny- 64deg F- Many fluffy clouds- light east breeze- Pair of Loons- no other boats on lake- Heavy rain on Thur + Friday
Nice sunny day (84 deg F.)few clouds-slight breeze. Two Mallard ducks- one Blue Heron and one other boat on lake.
Beautiful day (86 deg F.)medium breeze- sunny with very few clouds. No other boats on lake. One swimming Loon

Total overcast (67 deg F.)calm- no breeze at all. One other fishing boat on lake. Temperature gauge appeared to be faulty even though battery tested OK. The temperatures I've listed are probably not correct but they are what were noted.
Sunny- 74 deg F- mild wind no clouds. Very beautiful day- no other boats on lake- two Loons. ( Used new depth finder)
Perfect day 80 deg F.- billowy white clouds- sailboat on lake. Bald Eagle overhead. Jet skiers on the 4th- Heavy rain during previous night. (Chem. also)
61 deg F.-Mild wind full overcast. 20 Mergansers on lake- no other boats- no other birds. Previous week was very windy. (Chem. also)
78 deg F and sunny most of the day. No one else on the lake- water looks very clear. Storm passing to the south- mild N.W. wind- billowy clouds.

77 deg F- hazy overcast- light breeze from the S.W.-2 other boats on lake

Sunny 72 deg F- 2-Kayaks- 2-fishing boats- several swimmers on east beach and at Bartman's. No birds on Lake. No Pier at public boat landing. Water very low.
Sunny with few clouds 73 deg F- 1- fishing boat- no swimmers- light breeze

Partly cloudly 70 deg F.- little breezy- rained all night- no other boats on lake- beautiful day. No Loons or other water birds on lake. Bald Eagle watching us the whole time we were on the lake from his perch on the south end.
Beautiful day-partly cloudy. Heavy rail last few days. No other boats on lake. One Loon and no other birds. 74deg.
No clouds- 69 deg + windy. No other boats on lake. Bald Eagle at tree top at South end of lake.

column1: Digital Thermometer checked out at 32 deg in ice water and 190.4 deg in boiling water. close enough.

column2: Slight overcast- beautiful Fall day. 65 deg- light breeze. Bald Eagle at top of tree at South end of lake again. Four Merganzers swimming along on West side of lake. No other boats. Unusually warm weather for October but very nice.

Jim +Pat Allen collected and entered all data. Hot sunny and clear 90 deg F. .One pleasure boat on lake. Previous night we had high winds- thunder- lightning- and rain. 3-Loons on lake. The lake is the clearest I've seen in many years. No algae visable. The lake is about 8 to 9 inches higher than October of 2010.

column1: About 75 deg F. very sunny with few clouds.  Two mature and one immature Bald Eagle out today in the northwest bay.  The Lake was very wavy yesterday. So much so that I could not maintain my spot by the deep hole and had to forego the Secchi readings. No other boats on the lake today.

column2: About 68 deg F.-Quite windy-partly cloudy. 2 Bald Eagles overhead + 2 fishermen on lake. Weather over week has varied from 55 to 85 deg F.
